      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "b1a8c9badab38dc6",
      "text": "If a child enjoys running through the outgoing waves on the seashore – is that a game? It can become a game – what must be added? Why can we call both chess and a dreamy pushing around of colorful stones a game? One can play almost anytime. An everydayness, then, but an everyday possible experience of the extra-ordinary. What is extra-ordinary about it? What do we do when we play?\n\n"
    },
